WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:29.997 --> 00:32.631
         No, wait, wait.

00:32.732 --> 00:33.799
              Wait!

00:33.901 --> 00:36.201
            - Shh...
           - Come on.

00:36.303 --> 00:38.570
             - Stop.
      - No, no, it's okay.

00:38.672 --> 00:40.205
        - You can do it.
             - Stop!

00:40.307 --> 00:41.740
               No!

00:41.842 --> 00:44.143
             Yes...

00:45.579 --> 00:47.012
              - No!
            - Shh...

00:47.114 --> 00:49.348
             No! No!

00:52.153 --> 00:53.585
              Stop!

00:54.855 --> 00:57.489
         [siren wailing]

00:59.627 --> 01:01.627
   NURSE: How are you feeling?

01:05.166 --> 01:07.366
  Can I get you anything else?

01:10.404 --> 01:13.138
     Do you want to tell me
         what happened?

01:18.345 --> 01:20.112
              Okay.

01:20.214 --> 01:23.215
       I'm sorry, but this
     might be a little cold.

01:34.061 --> 01:35.427
              Good.

01:47.108 --> 01:48.974
    You, you stay right here,
            sweetie.

01:49.076 --> 01:52.077
      I'll be back for you
     in just a minute, okay?

02:03.724 --> 02:05.891
          Kennedy High
     may be a public school,

02:05.993 --> 02:08.994
      but we're not immune
 to fluctuations of the economy.

02:09.096 --> 02:12.631
     We certainly appreciate
 your philanthropy, Mr. Andrews.

02:12.733 --> 02:14.466
        Both my law firm
          and my family

02:14.568 --> 02:17.569
      have always believed
    in doing our civic duty.

02:17.671 --> 02:19.872
        Now I have never
      come across a school,

02:19.974 --> 02:21.507
       public or private,

02:21.609 --> 02:23.909
        that couldn't use
an upgrade to its IT department.

02:24.011 --> 02:25.911
        The students will
        be very grateful.

02:26.013 --> 02:28.213
    Most of their cell phones
        are more advanced

02:28.315 --> 02:30.249
   than any computers we have.

02:30.351 --> 02:32.317
          I can't wait
    to share this with them.

02:32.419 --> 02:35.420
  Well, here's to fresh starts.

02:35.523 --> 02:39.992
     Now, Chris, I have been
   reviewing your transcripts,

02:40.094 --> 02:44.329
         and may I say,
        very impressive.

02:44.431 --> 02:46.465
          Academically.

02:49.003 --> 02:50.269
        Thank you, ma'am.

02:50.371 --> 02:52.704
       And I tend to agree
        with your mother.

02:52.806 --> 02:56.275
        Everyone deserves
        a second chance.

03:00.281 --> 03:01.813
 Welcome to Kennedy High, Chris.

03:05.119 --> 03:08.487
  Thank you, Principal Atkins.

03:14.562 --> 03:16.562
      Well, one more year,
   and it's goodbye, Kennedy.

03:16.664 --> 03:18.530
   And not a moment too soon.

03:18.632 --> 03:20.399
     Come on, it hasn't been
            that bad.

03:20.501 --> 03:23.569
  Please. Same boring classes,
    same brain-dead teachers,

03:23.671 --> 03:25.437
     same two-faced friends.

03:25.539 --> 03:27.706
     College, here we come.

03:35.115 --> 03:37.316
          [horn blares]

03:49.029 --> 03:50.929
        See? This is what
       I'm talking about.

03:51.031 --> 03:52.397
     If we were in college,

03:52.499 --> 03:54.333
      we could be going out
       for sushi or froyo,

03:54.435 --> 03:57.269
     instead of being forced
   to eat here like prisoners.

03:57.371 --> 03:59.438
   What are you talking about?
    We have tons of choices.

03:59.540 --> 04:02.941
You want frozen chicken patties,
   fish sticks, or gray beef?

04:03.043 --> 04:04.710
           [chuckles]

04:12.253 --> 04:14.353
    Was it something I said?

04:16.890 --> 04:18.156
         Chris Andrews.

04:18.259 --> 04:19.224
             Riley.

04:21.428 --> 04:22.561
            It's Kim.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.164
         Uh, first day?

04:26.267 --> 04:27.566
           First day.

04:28.902 --> 04:30.335
         Just move here?

04:30.437 --> 04:31.870
               No.

04:35.109 --> 04:38.443
    Listen, you two look like
        the kind of girls

04:38.545 --> 04:40.045
       who know the story
          around here.

04:40.147 --> 04:41.213
              Okay.

04:41.315 --> 04:43.849
    My parents go away a lot.

04:43.951 --> 04:46.118
    I was thinking of having
      a party this weekend.

04:46.220 --> 04:47.552
    Good way to meet people.

04:47.655 --> 04:49.521
       You think you could
     spread the word for me?

04:49.623 --> 04:52.624
 - You came to the right place.
             - Good.

05:00.034 --> 05:01.867
        It's my address.

05:07.541 --> 05:09.641
        See you Saturday.

05:11.945 --> 05:13.211
               Oh.

05:14.815 --> 05:19.151
         I have a pool,
      so bring your suits.

05:20.487 --> 05:21.553
             Or not.

05:27.328 --> 05:31.063
  And suddenly, things just got
     a lot more interesting.

05:31.165 --> 05:34.166
   Uh, do I need to remind you
   about your boyfriend Matt?

05:34.268 --> 05:35.500
              Who?

05:35.602 --> 05:37.836
            [laughs]

05:37.938 --> 05:41.206
    <i> ♪ This could be the best</i>
       <i> we've ever known ♪</i>

05:41.308 --> 05:44.376
     <i> ♪ It's all behind us ♪</i>

05:44.478 --> 05:47.979
         <i> ♪♪ [continues]</i>

05:55.956 --> 05:59.291
            <i> ♪♪ [rap]</i>

06:02.730 --> 06:04.930
     Don't you ever call me
          melodramatic.

06:05.032 --> 06:06.965
           Do you know
     how insulting that is?

06:07.067 --> 06:09.267
           Okay, okay,
  I didn't mean anything by it.

06:09.370 --> 06:10.869
        I just meant that
     you were overreacting.

06:10.971 --> 06:12.237
   You were getting all upset

06:12.339 --> 06:13.538
         over something
     that wasn't a big deal.

06:13.640 --> 06:15.207
        I'm glad to hear
         that you think

06:15.309 --> 06:17.109
        our relationship
        isn't a big deal.

06:17.211 --> 06:19.111
 That's not what I meant at all,
        and you know it.

06:19.213 --> 06:21.046
         - She's a slut.
       - She's not a slut.

06:21.148 --> 06:23.448
  Those are just stupid rumors,
           that's it.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.118
           Oh, so now
      you're defending her.

06:26.220 --> 06:28.920
  - No, I'm not defending her.
  - Then what about the photos?

06:29.022 --> 06:31.123
     What about the photos?
   They didn't show anything.

06:31.225 --> 06:32.824
 We were talking to each other,
           that's all.

06:32.926 --> 06:35.494
     She looked pretty happy
   to have just been talking.

06:35.596 --> 06:36.962
      Okay, I think you've
      had enough to drink.

06:37.064 --> 06:39.231
           I'll decide
      when I've had enough.

06:39.333 --> 06:40.832
        It's a good look
         for you, Riley.

06:40.934 --> 06:43.402
You should be proud of yourself.

06:43.504 --> 06:45.504
         I'm outta here.

06:50.244 --> 06:51.476
           Go to hell.

06:56.517 --> 06:57.649
          [door closes]

06:59.219 --> 07:01.586
         <i> ♪♪ [continues]</i>

08:42.556 --> 08:45.357
 Here. It'll take the edge off.

08:45.459 --> 08:47.759
 I already have one, thank you.

08:47.861 --> 08:50.362
         You don't seem
      like the kind of girl

08:50.464 --> 08:52.597
      who deserves to drink
           warm beer.

08:52.699 --> 08:54.966
            Come on.

08:58.005 --> 08:59.404
      It's the good stuff.

08:59.506 --> 09:02.874
      It's from my parents'
         liquor cabinet.

09:02.976 --> 09:04.943
           What is it?

09:06.046 --> 09:07.145
             Drink.

09:13.887 --> 09:15.353
            No good?

09:17.157 --> 09:19.558
  If I told you how much people
 like my father and his friends

09:19.660 --> 09:21.993
        pay for a bottle
         of that stuff,

09:22.095 --> 09:25.630
        you'd think I was
     stoned out of my mind.

09:25.732 --> 09:27.399
     Where are your parents?

09:30.237 --> 09:32.337
             Aspen.

09:32.439 --> 09:36.808
      Maybe Vail, but that
    could've been last week.

09:36.910 --> 09:39.110
 They could be in the Caribbean,

09:39.212 --> 09:41.980
     I remember them saying
    Saint something or other.

09:42.082 --> 09:43.748
    What do your parents do?

09:45.352 --> 09:46.651
           Make money.

09:46.753 --> 09:48.486
           [chuckles]

10:25.559 --> 10:27.659
          RILEY: Whoa.

10:27.761 --> 10:29.194
           [chuckling]

10:29.296 --> 10:30.528
             Kimmy!

10:30.631 --> 10:32.097
            Come on.
        You ready to go?

10:32.199 --> 10:35.500
     You know Chris, right?

10:40.841 --> 10:42.073
            Let's go.

10:42.175 --> 10:45.010
           No, no, no.
       We can't leave yet.

10:45.112 --> 10:50.248
      Chris was telling me
    all about his house in...

10:50.350 --> 10:53.885
           - Caramel.
            - Carmel.

10:53.987 --> 10:56.154
             Right!

10:56.256 --> 10:58.390
 You know, I can drive her home
        when she's ready.

10:58.492 --> 11:00.892
   I think I'll take her now,
             thanks.

11:00.994 --> 11:05.864
 But I want to stay with Chris.

11:05.966 --> 11:07.766
              See?

11:07.868 --> 11:09.901
     Besides, it'll give her
      a chance to sober up.

11:10.003 --> 11:13.838
     I'm sure you don't want
  to bring her home like this.

11:16.877 --> 11:18.576
    You sure you'll be okay?

11:18.679 --> 11:20.478
            [giggles]

11:24.685 --> 11:26.718
     Make sure she gets home
           all right.

11:30.590 --> 11:32.857
            [giggles]

11:37.364 --> 11:53.311
       Come on, let's go.

11:57.350 --> 11:59.017
        Watch your step.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.529
           Right here.

12:13.366 --> 12:14.632
               Up.

12:39.392 --> 12:40.358
              Hey.

12:42.362 --> 12:43.328
             [click]

12:43.430 --> 12:44.829
             - Stop.
           - Come on.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.431
              Stop.

12:49.035 --> 12:50.435
             - Stop.
        - Come on, baby.

12:50.537 --> 12:52.003
        Aren't you ready
       for your close-up?

12:52.105 --> 12:53.538
             - Stop.
             - Hmm?

13:12.526 --> 13:13.792
               Ah.

13:21.134 --> 13:23.067
         <i> ♪♪ [continues]</i>

13:23.170 --> 13:26.838
      <i> ♪ Together, feel it</i>
         <i> Make it real ♪</i>

13:26.940 --> 13:29.808
            <i> ♪ This ♪</i>

13:29.910 --> 13:32.644
      <i> ♪ Paradise is home ♪</i>

13:34.381 --> 13:37.582
  <i> ♪ Making paradise our home ♪</i>

13:39.786 --> 13:42.453
      <i> ♪ Paradise is home ♪</i>

13:44.925 --> 13:45.990
            [groans]

13:51.498 --> 13:52.730
            [grunts]

13:58.972 --> 14:00.338
            [groans]

14:13.687 --> 14:15.587
         <i> [line ringing]</i>

14:15.689 --> 14:17.422
         <i> This is Matt.</i>
      <i> You know what to do.</i>

14:17.524 --> 14:18.523
             <i> [beep]</i>

14:18.625 --> 14:20.758
          Hey, it's me.

14:20.861 --> 14:23.895
       I feel like death.

14:23.997 --> 14:25.530
           I'm sorry.

14:25.632 --> 14:27.999
          Can we talk?

14:28.101 --> 14:30.935
       Call me. Okay, bye.

15:32.799 --> 15:34.232
            [groans]

15:37.103 --> 15:38.870
       Morning, sunshine.

15:38.972 --> 15:41.506
       Ha ha. Very funny.

15:41.608 --> 15:43.441
       Since when did you
     start drinking coffee?

15:43.543 --> 15:46.010
     Since my head felt like
      it was gonna explode.

15:46.112 --> 15:47.545
       I hope you weren't
         doing anything

15:47.647 --> 15:49.380
      you weren't supposed
     to be doing last night.

15:49.482 --> 15:50.949
        Mom, can you just
        give me a break?

15:51.051 --> 15:52.817
    I didn't get much sleep.

15:52.919 --> 15:55.620
    I was so tired from work,
 I didn't even hear you come in.

15:55.722 --> 15:58.823
   What time did you get home?

15:58.925 --> 16:00.758
              Huh?

16:00.860 --> 16:02.961
       I don't know. Late.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.131
      You got plans today?

16:07.233 --> 16:09.467
    I've got some work to do.

16:09.569 --> 16:12.503
    Maybe I'll go for a run,
       hang out with Kim.

16:12.605 --> 16:14.305
  Well, have fun, but remember

16:14.407 --> 16:16.841
    I have dinner with Robert
 tonight, so you're on your own.

16:16.943 --> 16:18.076
              What?

16:18.178 --> 16:20.078
       He's so weird, Mom.

16:20.180 --> 16:24.415
         He's not weird.
        He's just quirky.

16:24.517 --> 16:27.652
 Okay, those thick clear glasses
  look like a serial killer's,

16:27.754 --> 16:31.689
        and he's got like
 the worst weave I've ever seen.

16:31.791 --> 16:34.926
           [laughing]
         Listen, kiddo.

16:37.864 --> 16:39.764
   When you get to be my age,

16:39.866 --> 16:41.899
     your gonna see that not
    every guy has a six-pack

16:42.002 --> 16:43.501
    and a thick head of hair.

16:43.603 --> 16:45.370
    Okay, now, I've gotta go.

16:45.472 --> 16:48.039
Where are you going? You usually
     don't work all weekend.

16:48.141 --> 16:49.674
         Denise asked me
       to cover her shift.

16:49.776 --> 16:51.943
   She picked up a little bug
     in the children's wing.

16:52.045 --> 16:53.611
     You're always covering
          for someone.

16:53.713 --> 16:55.046
   Well, we can use the money,

16:55.148 --> 16:57.015
     especially with college
           next year.

16:57.117 --> 17:00.585
     I told you, I could get
  a part-time job like Kim has.

17:00.687 --> 17:04.255
  Your job is to study, so you
   can get into a good school.

17:04.357 --> 17:08.459
  Why can't you just find some
  rich doctor at the hospital?

17:08.560 --> 17:10.294
        I'm sure they're
       crawling with 'em.

17:10.396 --> 17:13.598
  [sighs] Because the best ones
          are married.

17:13.700 --> 17:15.199
     Who's talking marriage?

17:15.300 --> 17:18.469
         Who raised you?
          You're so...

17:18.570 --> 17:21.339
       Okay, so hot water,
   Tabasco sauce, and ginger.

17:21.441 --> 17:24.375
  It works every time, okay?
      Now I've got to go.

18:53.933 --> 18:57.268
  - My mom knew I was hungover.
        - Was she pissed?

18:57.370 --> 19:01.405
 No, but I'll probably get some
    fake, spontaneous lecture

19:01.508 --> 19:03.941
      about responsibility
          and maturity.

19:04.043 --> 19:05.843
    She just needs some time
         to work on it.

19:05.945 --> 19:08.212
      Maybe you deserve it.

19:08.314 --> 19:10.414
         How bad was I?

19:10.517 --> 19:12.250
              Bad.

19:12.352 --> 19:14.385
          Don't worry.
     Everyone was so wasted,

19:14.487 --> 19:16.587
  they probably don't remember.

19:16.689 --> 19:20.324
    I just don't understand.
     I never get like that.

19:20.426 --> 19:22.960
   At least you got home okay.

19:24.998 --> 19:26.063
             Right?

19:26.166 --> 19:28.766
         Yeah, I mean...

19:28.868 --> 19:30.701
        Yeah, I guess so.

19:30.803 --> 19:33.905
         I really don't
       remember anything.

19:34.007 --> 19:37.642
       You don't remember
     Chris taking you home?

19:37.744 --> 19:39.644
      What do you remember?

19:39.746 --> 19:42.547
 I remember the fight with Matt,

19:42.649 --> 19:44.382
     hanging out with Chris
          by the pool,

19:44.484 --> 19:47.718
           telling you
    I wanted to stay, then...

19:47.820 --> 19:51.122
     nothing until I woke up
          this morning.

19:51.224 --> 19:52.456
   I shouldn't have left you.

19:52.559 --> 19:54.559
       It wasn't your job
         to babysit me.

19:54.661 --> 19:57.395
    It was my choice to stay.

19:57.497 --> 20:00.064
  Matt won't talk to me though.

20:00.166 --> 20:01.432
         What'd he say?

20:01.534 --> 20:03.434
      Didn't say anything.

20:03.536 --> 20:06.270
     Won't answer my calls,
     won't return my texts.

20:06.372 --> 20:07.672
       He'll get over it.

20:07.774 --> 20:09.674
      You guys always have
       these little spats.

20:09.776 --> 20:11.909
              Yeah.

20:12.011 --> 20:14.712
      Yeah, I guess we do.

20:16.616 --> 20:18.416
               So?

20:18.518 --> 20:20.851
            So what?

20:20.954 --> 20:23.921
         Riley, come on,
     you're my best friend.

20:24.023 --> 20:25.756
            Did you?

20:25.858 --> 20:29.493
  A lady doesn't kiss and tell.

20:38.871 --> 20:40.838
          [horn blares]

20:53.052 --> 20:55.620
        How long were you
     planning to ignore me?

20:55.722 --> 20:57.188
  I have nothing to say to you.

20:57.290 --> 20:58.856
     I wanted to apologize,

20:58.958 --> 21:00.992
      if you weren't being
      such a jerk about it.

21:01.094 --> 21:02.960
      Oh, I'm being a jerk?

21:03.062 --> 21:04.695
First, you accuse me of flirting
        with Laura Lewis,

21:04.797 --> 21:06.497
  then you make a complete fool
    of yourself at the party,

21:06.599 --> 21:09.200
   then you go and cheat on me
   with that rich pretty boy.

21:09.302 --> 21:10.534
  Wait, wait, wait, slow down.

21:10.637 --> 21:12.069
      What the hell are you
         talking about?

21:12.171 --> 21:14.572
         Come on, Riley,
  don't pull this crap with me.

21:14.674 --> 21:17.041
     I swear. I have no idea
   what you're talking about.

21:18.711 --> 21:21.445
    Someone sent these to me
           last night.

21:30.590 --> 21:32.723
    I don't know what to say.

21:34.127 --> 21:35.726
     That's what I thought.

21:35.828 --> 21:36.994
              Matt!

21:38.831 --> 21:39.964
              What?

21:40.066 --> 21:41.732
            Nothing.

21:56.215 --> 21:57.682
         Hi, sweetheart.

21:57.784 --> 21:59.750
          Where's Bob?

21:59.852 --> 22:02.320
         Thanks to you,
       throughout dinner,

22:02.422 --> 22:04.989
    I couldn't stop thinking
        about the weave.

22:07.794 --> 22:11.696
     Anyway, we just decided
  to take a break for a while.

22:11.798 --> 22:13.464
      Not because of that.

22:13.566 --> 22:16.467
     No, but it didn't help.

22:16.569 --> 22:18.369
           I'm sorry.

22:18.471 --> 22:22.740
      Ah, men come and go.
           You'll see.

22:22.842 --> 22:24.475
       How was your night?

22:24.577 --> 22:25.876
              Fine.

22:25.978 --> 22:27.311
      Did you do anything?

22:27.413 --> 22:29.747
     Just eat and watch TV.

22:29.849 --> 22:31.615
            No Matt?

22:31.718 --> 22:34.552
       Don't pretend like
       you don't like him.

22:34.654 --> 22:36.420
         I do like him.

22:36.522 --> 22:38.622
         You're just...
      You're just so young.

22:38.725 --> 22:41.692
  Mom, I'm not getting married.
      I'm just having fun.

22:41.794 --> 22:43.561
That's what I'm concerned about.

22:47.500 --> 22:48.899
       Is anything wrong?

22:50.269 --> 22:52.670
     Just tired, that's all.

22:52.772 --> 22:55.740
    Okay. Well, on that note,
      I am going to turn in

22:55.842 --> 22:57.742
    because I have to get up
      really early for work

22:57.844 --> 22:59.009
        tomorrow morning.

22:59.112 --> 23:00.144
             Night.

23:00.246 --> 23:02.146
     Goodnight, sweetheart.

23:36.215 --> 23:37.748
          [sharp thud]

24:04.911 --> 24:07.645
        Mom, is that you?

25:12.211 --> 25:13.744
          [Riley sighs]

25:22.955 --> 25:25.289
        You have the most
         beautiful eyes.

25:25.391 --> 25:26.891
             - Do I?
             - Yeah.

25:26.993 --> 25:28.492
      They just draw me in.

25:28.594 --> 25:31.896
     You know, they say eyes
   are the window to the soul.

25:33.432 --> 25:35.633
        What in the hell
   do you think you're doing?

25:35.735 --> 25:36.901
             Okay...

25:37.003 --> 25:39.203
      Calm down, calm down.

25:39.305 --> 25:42.206
     We were just chatting.

25:42.308 --> 25:44.074
  Jealousy doesn't become you.

25:44.176 --> 25:46.710
      What did you do to me
         Saturday night?

25:46.812 --> 25:48.679
      What did I do to you?

25:48.781 --> 25:51.015
 I think it takes two to tango.

25:51.117 --> 25:53.384
    If I remember correctly,

25:53.486 --> 25:56.153
        it was mostly you
         doing it to me.

25:56.255 --> 25:57.488
          You're sick.

25:57.590 --> 25:59.823
          I don't know
      what the problem is.

25:59.926 --> 26:01.759
    We both had a great time.

