44:31.936 --> 44:33.403
 Tomorrow change all the locks.

44:33.505 --> 44:37.674
     After that, there's not
      much more we can do.

44:39.511 --> 44:40.943
           I'm sorry.

44:45.717 --> 44:47.350
 KIM: This is all totally crazy.

44:47.452 --> 44:49.118
 RILEY: What'd your parents say?

44:49.220 --> 44:50.720
   MATT: Oh, they were pissed.

44:50.822 --> 44:53.122
    Pissed at the detective,
   pissed at the other family.

44:53.224 --> 44:54.857
     My dad's not an idiot.

44:54.959 --> 44:56.559
     He knows we don't have
         a ton of money.

44:56.661 --> 44:57.794
         We can't afford
        expensive lawyers

44:57.896 --> 44:59.696
       to fight something
         we might lose.

44:59.798 --> 45:01.230
  Plus they're worried that if
 the colleges get wind of this,

45:01.332 --> 45:02.765
          I might lose
    some of my scholarships.

45:02.867 --> 45:05.935
         It's messed up
   that he can do this to us.

45:06.037 --> 45:07.937
    Your parents say anything
        to you about me?

45:08.039 --> 45:09.038
           Like what?

45:12.577 --> 45:14.944
 Something happened last night.

45:17.482 --> 45:21.484
  I was woken up in the middle
  of the night by a phone call.

45:21.586 --> 45:25.421
   Someone was Facetiming me,
  but I didn't know who it was.

45:25.523 --> 45:27.256
      I answered it anyway.

45:27.358 --> 45:29.292
        And? Who was it?

45:29.394 --> 45:32.628
         I couldn't see,

45:32.731 --> 45:34.997
 instead of pointing the camera
          at his face,

45:35.100 --> 45:37.500
      he decided to show me
         where he was at

45:37.602 --> 45:39.502
     and where he was going.

45:39.604 --> 45:40.670
          Where was he?

45:42.707 --> 45:44.240
       He was in my house.

45:44.342 --> 45:45.742
       Oh, my God, Riley!

45:45.844 --> 45:48.578
         I know, I know.
 I was about to call the police,

45:48.680 --> 45:50.747
    but I guess he heard me,

45:50.849 --> 45:52.281
  and he ran out of the house.

45:52.383 --> 45:53.750
          Are you okay?

45:53.852 --> 45:55.785
    I just don't understand.

45:55.887 --> 45:57.253
       He had gotten off.

45:57.355 --> 45:59.522
        After the video,
 it was me that got in trouble.

45:59.624 --> 46:00.957
     Why would he risk this?

46:01.059 --> 46:03.226
          Because he's
     a freaking psychopath.

46:04.796 --> 46:05.962
          The photos of
      you and Laura Lewis,

46:06.064 --> 46:07.930
    the ones I got mad about,

46:08.032 --> 46:10.700
        who do you think
posted those on the school wiki?

46:10.802 --> 46:12.835
  I didn't even think about it.

46:12.937 --> 46:15.304
         I was too busy
    trying to calm you down.

46:15.406 --> 46:16.973
 Riley, what are you getting at?

46:17.075 --> 46:18.775
       It had to be Chris,

46:18.877 --> 46:21.244
           and he knew
    it would lead to a fight.

46:22.814 --> 46:25.281
   That means he targeted you
       from the beginning.

46:25.383 --> 46:27.316
        But why? Why you?

46:27.418 --> 46:29.552
Like you said, after he got away
        with the attack,

46:29.654 --> 46:31.354
   why break into your house?

46:31.456 --> 46:33.489
            Exactly.

46:33.591 --> 46:36.692
 The problem is, we don't really
    know anything about him.

46:36.795 --> 46:38.194
  He just showed up at school.

46:38.296 --> 46:40.563
         I have an idea.

46:42.000 --> 46:43.966
 We need to know more about him.

46:44.068 --> 46:47.370
           He's crazy,
      but he's not stupid.

46:48.940 --> 46:51.007
       Matt can't pretend
     to be friends with him,

46:51.109 --> 46:53.176
      and if Riley suddenly
     has a change of heart,

46:53.278 --> 46:57.246
      well, he's not gonna
      believe that either.

46:57.348 --> 46:58.748
       So that leaves me.

46:58.850 --> 47:00.850
           I'm sorry,
       I don't understand.

47:00.952 --> 47:04.053
      I get close to Chris,
      pretend I'm into him.

47:04.155 --> 47:06.689
    I can convince him of it.
          I know I can.

47:06.791 --> 47:08.424
 Kim, you played a flying monkey

47:08.526 --> 47:09.892
     during our kindergarten
           production

47:09.994 --> 47:11.194
      of <i> The Wizard of Oz,</i>

47:11.296 --> 47:12.929
        and now suddenly
       you're an actress?

47:13.031 --> 47:14.463
   I sold that flying monkey.

47:16.334 --> 47:18.568
       Besides, Chris will
       never fall for it.

47:18.670 --> 47:20.203
  He knows we're best friends.

47:20.305 --> 47:22.438
       And in high school,
   people change best friends

47:22.540 --> 47:24.273
        like they change
        their underwear.

47:24.375 --> 47:26.108
    He is an arrogant S-O-B.

47:26.211 --> 47:29.045
  Meaning he's so narcissistic,

47:29.147 --> 47:31.280
  he might actually believe it.

47:33.351 --> 47:34.951
           Forget it.
       It's too dangerous.

47:35.053 --> 47:37.553
 If he's crazy enough to do that
         to his own face

47:37.655 --> 47:41.023
  and sick enough to try to do
       what he did to me,

47:41.125 --> 47:44.560
  I don't even want to imagine
      what he's capable of.

47:44.662 --> 47:47.263
  Riley, you're my best friend.

47:47.365 --> 47:50.633
         He's after you,
    and he's not gonna stop.

47:53.404 --> 47:56.105
           Look at me.

47:56.207 --> 47:58.374
         I'm doing this.

47:59.911 --> 48:02.245
         I told you it's
   none of your business, Kim.

48:02.347 --> 48:03.880
      You're not my mother.

48:03.982 --> 48:06.949
    No, but I'm your friend.
    At least I thought I was.

48:07.051 --> 48:08.451
        And you're acting
      like such a selfish--

48:08.553 --> 48:11.988
      A what? What? Say it.

48:12.090 --> 48:15.291
 Riley, I'm sick of your drama.
          I really am.

48:15.393 --> 48:16.726
 Why don't you go talk to Matt?

48:16.828 --> 48:18.594
        He's the only one
        who believes you.

48:18.696 --> 48:20.796
     You're a loser, Kimmy.

48:20.899 --> 48:22.398
       If you think you're
     so much better than me,

48:22.500 --> 48:24.066
    go find some new friends.

48:24.168 --> 48:27.236
     See if they put up with
    your self-righteous crap.

48:35.680 --> 48:38.147
             - Hey.
          - Hey to you.

48:41.185 --> 48:44.820
       It's just sometimes
       she can be such a--

48:44.923 --> 48:47.356
           Never mind.
        I'm just pissed.

48:49.193 --> 48:53.529
       She takes advantage
of your friendship, doesn't she?

48:53.631 --> 48:55.131
        You have no idea.

48:55.233 --> 48:57.533
      Expects you to always
        be there for her.

48:57.635 --> 49:00.603
       She's there for you
   only when it's convenient.

49:00.705 --> 49:04.774
 Otherwise, all she cares about
  is her boyfriend and herself.

49:04.876 --> 49:07.643
        I've let her walk
       all over me since--

49:07.745 --> 49:10.846
    I'm sorry. I'm not gonna
  bother you with my problems.

49:12.650 --> 49:14.550
    How are you getting home?

49:14.652 --> 49:16.319
         I usually walk.

49:16.421 --> 49:19.322
 I don't live too far from here.
       I don't have a car.

49:19.424 --> 49:22.224
          I have a car.

49:22.327 --> 49:23.492
            Oh, yeah?

49:23.594 --> 49:25.061
              Yeah.

49:26.264 --> 49:27.730
            Come on.

49:48.987 --> 49:51.253
    What'd you win this for?

49:51.356 --> 49:54.557
           Who knows?
      One thing or another.

50:01.432 --> 50:03.632
  How long have you lived here?

50:05.503 --> 50:07.737
      Almost my whole life.

50:10.441 --> 50:14.110
    Where'd you go to school
         before Kennedy?

50:14.212 --> 50:16.679
         Is this really
   what you wanna talk about?

50:20.084 --> 50:23.019
      You know, I normally
         don't do this,

50:23.121 --> 50:26.922
 just come to some guy's house.

50:27.025 --> 50:29.125
       We're just talking.

50:29.227 --> 50:31.594
   Besides, I get the feeling
     you're tired of people

50:31.696 --> 50:33.195
     telling you what to do.

50:38.069 --> 50:40.269
    I know this sounds crazy,

50:40.371 --> 50:44.106
 but in some ways, it seems like
   you know me better than...

50:45.977 --> 50:47.977
             than...

50:48.079 --> 50:49.245
           Never mind.

50:55.420 --> 50:56.919
      That's because I do.

50:57.021 --> 51:01.390
     We're a lot alike, Kim,
           you and I.

51:05.329 --> 51:06.796
            Tell me.

51:06.898 --> 51:09.565
         I need to know.

51:09.667 --> 51:11.867
        Did you really do
        what Riley says?

51:11.969 --> 51:15.104
     Force yourself on her?

51:25.216 --> 51:27.850
 Do I look like the kind of guy
       who would do that?

51:32.290 --> 51:35.858
       She's always trying
        to get attention.

51:35.960 --> 51:38.661
   Doesn't care who she hurts.

51:42.600 --> 51:45.634
        I think it's time
  someone taught her a lesson.

51:52.477 --> 51:55.111
         - [horn honks]
      - [car alarm blaring]

51:55.213 --> 51:56.579
            Damn it.

51:56.681 --> 51:58.080
           What is it?

51:58.182 --> 52:01.217
  [blaring, honking continues]

52:05.189 --> 52:06.122
           [clicking]

52:06.224 --> 52:09.258
  [blaring, honking continues]

52:09.360 --> 52:10.860
             [beep]

52:17.535 --> 52:18.868
             [click]

52:30.381 --> 52:32.047
               No.

52:32.150 --> 52:34.884
           No, no, no!

52:34.986 --> 52:37.386
            [panting]

52:41.559 --> 52:42.658
             [click]

52:58.176 --> 52:59.208
          [Chris yells]

53:00.444 --> 53:03.245
   What is it? What happened?

53:03.347 --> 53:05.814
       They keyed my car.

53:05.917 --> 53:10.019
    Who did? Riley and Matt?

53:10.121 --> 53:11.787
            Who else?

53:11.889 --> 53:13.789
   We have to call the police.
   Who do they think they are?

53:13.891 --> 53:16.025
  There's no proof it was them.

53:16.127 --> 53:17.793
  Well, maybe someone saw them,
      or they left a clue.

53:17.895 --> 53:20.095
         We have to try.

53:20.198 --> 53:23.399
        Especially after
    what they accused you of.

53:26.771 --> 53:30.272
          Don't worry.
      I'll take care of it.

53:31.576 --> 53:33.175
        What do you mean?

53:36.247 --> 53:40.049
   I mean sometimes there are
  better ways to handle things

53:40.151 --> 53:42.518
    than going to the police.

53:44.388 --> 53:46.922
    Well, you're a lot calmer
        than I would be.

53:48.859 --> 53:51.093
       I'd make them pay.

53:55.967 --> 53:57.466
           [rustling]

53:57.568 --> 54:00.135
        RILEY: You okay?
      KIM: Yeah. You guys?

54:00.238 --> 54:02.871
   We're fine. It was a cinch.

54:02.974 --> 54:05.474
      I might have a career
         as a locksmith.

54:05.576 --> 54:07.743
     - He was really pissed?
           - Royally.

54:07.845 --> 54:09.712
    But he didn't touch you,
        didn't hurt you?

54:09.814 --> 54:12.248
         No. I made sure
      he kept his distance.

54:12.350 --> 54:15.017
- You really think he bought it?
   - I'm absolutely convinced

54:15.119 --> 54:17.853
            he thinks
  I can't stand either of you.

54:17.955 --> 54:20.322
   He thought he was so smart,
     like he was uncovering

54:20.424 --> 54:22.391
   some deep-seated resentment
         I had for you.

54:22.493 --> 54:23.525
        Ooh, that's deep.

54:23.628 --> 54:24.727
          Maybe you do.

54:24.829 --> 54:26.128
           [chuckles]

54:30.134 --> 54:32.901
          The thing is,
      while I was with him,

54:33.004 --> 54:35.337
    it was completely obvious

54:35.439 --> 54:37.506
        how manipulative
        and crazy he was,

54:37.608 --> 54:40.309
      but I wasn't scared.

54:41.946 --> 54:43.679
 In fact, it was kind of weird.

54:43.781 --> 54:45.781
    It was almost reassuring
         to be with him.

54:45.883 --> 54:49.118
   How do you think sociopaths
  manage to get their victims?

54:49.220 --> 54:51.253
        They're charming.

54:51.355 --> 54:53.355
       On second thought,
     it makes my skin crawl.

54:53.457 --> 54:55.391
      So what do we do now?

54:55.493 --> 54:57.259
You got the pictures I sent you?

54:57.361 --> 54:59.428
   Yep. Nothing too revealing.

54:59.530 --> 55:01.463
    The info on his license,
        we already knew,

55:01.565 --> 55:05.100
  and the other stuff was just
    generic, personal things.

55:05.202 --> 55:08.103
        Damn. I'm sorry.
     I did the best I could.

55:08.205 --> 55:10.773
     No, no, you were great.
      There was one thing.

55:10.875 --> 55:13.075
          The yearbook.
It says "Daedalus" on the cover.

55:13.177 --> 55:14.610
      I did a quick search,
        and it looks like

55:14.712 --> 55:16.478
     it's from St. Joseph's.

55:16.580 --> 55:19.815
   It's a private school about
  20 miles from here, up north.

55:19.917 --> 55:21.917
      He went there before
       he came to Kennedy.

55:22.019 --> 55:24.386
    Unless he's in the habit
 of collecting random yearbooks,

55:24.488 --> 55:25.454
              yeah.

55:25.556 --> 55:27.089
   Look, there's a kid I know,

55:27.191 --> 55:28.490
 went to football camp with him
       a few summers ago.

55:28.592 --> 55:30.159
         Parker McKeon.
        He's a good guy.

55:30.261 --> 55:32.761
      He goes to St. Joe's.
     I say we meet with him,

55:32.863 --> 55:34.263
     find out what he knows
          about Chris.

55:34.365 --> 55:35.998
   - Think he'll meet with us?
          - Of course.

55:36.100 --> 55:37.333
     He's a friend of mine.
   We hung out a lot at camp.

55:37.435 --> 55:38.434
       And if we're right,

55:38.536 --> 55:39.568
    he probably thinks Chris

55:39.670 --> 55:40.836
   is as big a dick as we do.

55:44.008 --> 55:45.474
             Riley.

55:45.576 --> 55:47.810
         I'm sorry about
  what I said the other night.

55:47.912 --> 55:50.312
          It was awful.

55:51.749 --> 55:53.282
        Thank you, honey.

55:53.384 --> 55:55.818
         But let's just
     forget about it, okay?

55:55.920 --> 55:57.986
    Dad is the one who left.

55:59.190 --> 56:01.590
        Dad. What a joke.

56:01.692 --> 56:03.292
      I mean, he's the one
      who walked out on us,

56:03.394 --> 56:06.462
       and you're the one
        that's been here

56:06.564 --> 56:08.263
    and given me everything,

56:08.366 --> 56:10.499
  and this is how I treat you?

56:10.601 --> 56:13.202
      Don't worry about it.
  It comes with the territory.

56:13.304 --> 56:15.204
    As far as I'm concerned,
         it's his loss.

56:15.306 --> 56:18.173
           After all,
     look what he's missing.

56:18.275 --> 56:20.976
  I hope I never see him again.

56:21.078 --> 56:22.478
    Otherwise, we might have
        to have a regular

56:22.580 --> 56:24.613
    Kramer vs. Kramer, right?

56:24.715 --> 56:26.448
           [laughing]

56:26.550 --> 56:29.017
    That's the stupidest joke
 every single time you tell it.

56:29.120 --> 56:31.620
       I haven't even seen
        that dumb movie.

56:31.722 --> 56:34.957
 Well, either way, I think we've
 been a pretty good team so far,

56:35.059 --> 56:37.226
           don't you?

56:37.328 --> 56:38.827
              - No.
              - No?

56:38.929 --> 56:40.229
        We've been great.

56:40.331 --> 56:41.764
           Come here.

56:44.802 --> 56:46.635
          - I gotta go.
             - Bye.

56:49.640 --> 56:50.539
            KIM: Hey.
         MATT: Hey, Kim.

56:50.641 --> 56:52.074
  KIM: I just talked to Chris.

56:52.176 --> 56:53.909
      He's at the body shop
       picking up his car.

56:54.011 --> 56:55.911
    MATT: Good, so we're safe
          to meet here.

56:56.013 --> 56:58.147
 I was thinking about something.

56:58.249 --> 57:00.716
     The other night when he
 Facetimed you, how'd he get in?

57:00.818 --> 57:02.818
    Yeah, how did he get in?

57:03.854 --> 57:05.320
         He had my keys.

57:05.423 --> 57:07.656
           I lost them
     the night of the party.

57:07.758 --> 57:09.725
        It's also how he
    must have gotten me home,

57:09.827 --> 57:11.293
  then he took them with them.

57:11.395 --> 57:12.828
    You didn't say anything.

57:12.930 --> 57:14.730
         I wasn't sure.

57:14.832 --> 57:17.399
        I was so wasted,
I figured I left them somewhere.

57:17.501 --> 57:19.101
      Then after the video,
  the last thing I wanted to do

57:19.203 --> 57:20.936
   was claim he stole my keys.

57:21.038 --> 57:23.405
  Riley, you gotta get your mom
     to change those locks.

57:23.507 --> 57:24.506
          She's right.

57:24.608 --> 57:26.308
        Hey, there he is.

57:27.745 --> 57:29.178
       Thanks for coming.
        Good to see you.

57:29.280 --> 57:30.913
            You too.

57:31.015 --> 57:33.749
    Parker McKeon, I want you
  to meet my girlfriend Riley,

57:33.851 --> 57:35.417
           and this is
      her best friend Kim.

57:35.519 --> 57:37.152
       Thanks for coming.

57:37.254 --> 57:39.321
   So listen, you know we want
 to ask you about Chris Andrews.

57:39.423 --> 57:41.757
   I know, and like we talked
       on the phone, dude,

57:41.859 --> 57:45.928
 I'll tell you everything I can,
but I didn't know him real well.

57:46.030 --> 57:47.796
            This him?

57:47.898 --> 57:49.598
        Yeah, that's him.

57:49.700 --> 57:51.533
  A lot of the girls liked him.

57:51.635 --> 57:55.037
   I guess he's good-looking,
    like really good-looking,

57:55.139 --> 57:57.339
         if you're into
       that kind of thing.

57:57.441 --> 57:58.874
        But I don't know.

57:58.976 --> 58:02.478
   He always seemed kind of...
         if you ask me.

58:02.580 --> 58:03.812
    And then what happened...

58:03.914 --> 58:05.614
        What did happen?

58:05.716 --> 58:07.316
       It was between him
   and this girl, Lisa Nelson.

58:07.418 --> 58:10.352
      She was nice, pretty.

58:10.454 --> 58:12.855
    But what happened, look,
    I heard a million things.

58:12.957 --> 58:15.224
     Who knows what's true?
     That's private school.

58:15.326 --> 58:16.658
         Everybody knows
      everybody's business,

58:16.760 --> 58:18.961
           or at least
       they think they do.

58:19.063 --> 58:20.629
       What did you hear?

58:20.731 --> 58:22.731
    According to some people,

58:22.833 --> 58:26.401
        he... forced her.

58:26.504 --> 58:28.470
   According to other people,

58:28.572 --> 58:30.005
  she was the kind of girl that
  didn't need much convincing,

58:30.107 --> 58:31.473
    if you know what I mean.

58:31.575 --> 58:33.542
      Did Lisa tell anyone?

58:33.644 --> 58:35.911
    PARKER: Yeah, the police
          investigated.

58:37.781 --> 58:39.982
     Chris got off, I think,

58:40.084 --> 58:42.150
     but he never came back
           to school.

58:42.253 --> 58:43.886
        What about Lisa?

58:45.556 --> 58:46.555
             [sighs]

59:13.717 --> 59:15.450
      [woman clears throat]

59:16.620 --> 59:17.886
           Ms. Nelson?

59:17.988 --> 59:18.954
              Yeah.

59:19.056 --> 59:21.456
  Hi. My name is Riley Cramer.

59:21.559 --> 59:24.593
I was hoping to speak with Lisa.

59:24.695 --> 59:26.595
   My daughter died last year.

59:28.866 --> 59:31.867
         I... I'm sorry.
         I had no idea.

59:31.969 --> 59:35.771
  Yeah, well, I'm gonna go back
to sleep now, if you don't mind.

59:35.873 --> 59:38.473
      Sorry for your loss.

59:38.576 --> 59:40.776
           Hey, uh...

59:40.878 --> 59:43.478
        since you already
   woke me up and everything,

59:43.581 --> 59:45.614
      why don't you tell me
         what you want?

59:45.716 --> 59:48.083
     It was nothing, really.

59:48.185 --> 59:51.954
  I had wanted to ask her about
   a former classmate of hers,

59:52.056 --> 59:53.922
   a boy named Chris Andrews.

59:54.024 --> 59:57.659
      A very dangerous boy.

01:00:00.998 --> 01:00:02.998
   Yeah, I don't usually sleep
          all day long,

01:00:03.100 --> 01:00:05.133
but I had two shifts last night,

01:00:05.235 --> 01:00:06.935
       and I didn't get in
        until 7:00, so...

01:00:07.037 --> 01:00:10.639
        No, no, um, I...

01:00:10.741 --> 01:00:12.808
      I'm just really sorry
        I disturbed you.

01:00:12.910 --> 01:00:14.409
         It's all right.

01:00:14.511 --> 01:00:16.945
       You said you wanted
